rComments: Jerie is a rockstar, best prof ever.
Jerie is truly amazing. Any class with her is a must. She's so helpful, clear and understanding! We need more communication profs like her - interesting, engaging and incredibly inspirational.

Jerie is one of my favourite professors at UOttawa. Her lectures are stimulating, fun, and interactive. It felt like a friend was lecturing me. Jerie is approachable, dedicated to helping students, and is very innovative in the classroom. Show up to class and participate. Photoshop was a pain at first but got better over time. Great class!

Jerie Shaw is by far one of the best professors I have ever had at UOttawa. She is approachable, cares about her students, provides incredible feedback, and is overall an amazing educator. Be sure to participate in her class and to do the readings before hand! I actually looked forward to attending her lectures.

Jerie is an amazing person and amazing prof. I've never encountered a more enthusiastic and invested professor who genuinely cares about her students understanding of the material . Be prepared to stay up to date with twice a week online readings and to work hard on the assignment, but you will definitely learn a lot. Highly recommend!

This is the BEST prof in the University of Ottawa. I recommend that every breathing being take this class. Her lectures are always fun and she teaches in a hands on way which makes the material more clear. Even her assignments are fun and I learned a lot! #Jerie4prez
Do your readings before class to pass the quiz. So there is a short quiz for every class and the readings are not long. Brief! Take this class and be happy :D

Readingslectures were done outside of class time via her PowerPoint vlogs (they're really short!) and the following lecture would have a short quiz based on the previous "reading" (easy and straight forward). Classes were discussionactivity based. It reinforced the material we learned through readings! Amazing teaching style. Take her classes!

Jerie is truly a breath of fresh air in comparison to many profs who assign lengthy readings and lecture by reading powerpoint. She truly cares about her students. She is a new prof so she is trying some new teaching methods; some work out better than others, but she always looks for our feedback after. Content is easy, just put the work in!

Classes were really well structured and the online teaching components were really well used to enhance learning. She was great at conveying content and the assignments (though long, and not overly easy) were extremely practical applications of the material. I really felt like I learned a lot in this course and had fun at the same time! A+

Jerie's a cool professor and gets a long with all of her students. But, she is an extremely hard grader and her work load was beyond overwhelming. She gives quizzes every class and is huge on participation so If you want an easy class & want to skip sometimes, DO NOT take her class. Being a graduate student, you'd think she'd cut us some slack.

Jerie is an amazing professor! Her innovative teaching methods made the course content interesting and memorable! She is always available to help and gives an incredible amount of feedback on assignments. It is clear that she wants her students to succeed. Also, I loved that there was no textbook :) Take as many courses as you can with her!

Jerie is seriously the best prof ever. I don't even know where to begin. If you are looking for a prof who genuinely cares about her students and wants them to do well, take her classes. You da best Jerie!
great prof!
she is very helpful and personable .

Jerie is unlike any Prof I've ever had. She uses an unconventional teaching style that makes in-class participation natural and effortless. She's great at introducing usefulpractical concepts in her class that are very applicable to everyday life. She is more than willing to help you out with whatever you bring to her. Do the work  good grades.

She's Fantastic!!  Her readings are like vlogs  ,but  with power point slides. You do quizzes in class after each reading so make sure you listen to them. She's really understanding and actually cares about her students. She's a modern thinking professor that lectures in a way that appeals to students based off their feedback. WE ALL LOVE JERIE!!!

Jerie is an awesome prof. You can truly see how much she cares about her students! She always goes the extra mile. A+ prof material. And although the content is easy, she makes sure to keep you up to date on readings and material by quizzing you each class, which I think is a great way to get fair marks and show effort.

Great class! I learned lots! This professor takes the time to not only teach the material, but also creates unique group activities to allow students to assess their own needs for improvement and gives the opportunity to enhance the skills of our peers.  There are readings and quizzes for every class, but I found myself looking forward to them.

Wow!!  She frames her class in order to give you life applicable skills, but does it with fun lectures and innovative group work.  She uses lots of tech savvy applications to enhance her courses, but includes multiple styles of teaching to cater to all learning styles.  She really cares about the material and wants you to understand.  So Helpful!!
